       BN_new() returns a pointer to the BBIIGGNNUUMM. If the
       allocation fails, it returns NNUULLLL and sets an error code
       that can be obtained by ERR_get_error(3).

       BN_init(), BN_clear(), BN_free() and BN_clear_free() have
       no return values.

